author: stsp
msg: (password_get_gpg_agent): Don't require GPG_TTY and TERM to be set in the
environment. These variables are only needed in some GPG Agent

author: stsp
msg: (password_set_gpg_agent): Don't require GPG_TTY to be set in the environment.
This variable is only needed in some GPG Agent configurations, and we should
allow other configurations to work as well. For example, a GUI app might
talk to GPG agent without a TTY. Apparently, this is the case on Mac OS X,
